### Health check
GET http://localhost:5000/health

### Send a simple pinch_down gesture (right hand)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/gesture
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "pinch_down",
  "hand": "right",
  "confidence": "0.92",
  "palmOrientation": "upright",
  "timestamp": "2025-09-13T12:00:00Z"
}

### Send a targeting gesture (left hand) with ray data
POST  http://localhost:5000/api/gesture
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "targeting",
  "hand": "left",
  "isValid": true,
  "rayOrigin": "(0.1, 1.2, -0.3)",
  "rayDirection": "(0.0, -1.0, 0.0)",
  "timestamp": "2025-09-13T12:00:10Z"
}

### Send a grab_begin gesture (toggle)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/gesture
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "grab_begin",
  "hand": "right",
  "timestamp": "2025-09-13T12:00:20Z"
}

### Send a state_change to STOP
POST http://localhost:5000/api/gesture
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "state_change",
  "state": "STOP",
  "timestamp": "2025-09-13T12:00:30Z"
}

### PowerShell curl example (for quick manual testing)
# Note: run this from PowerShell in the Backend directory
# Invoke-RestMethod -Uri http://localhost:5000/api/gesture -Method Post -ContentType 'application/json' -Body (ConvertTo-Json @{ type = 'pinch_down'; hand = 'right'; confidence = '0.9'; palmOrientation = 'upright' })

### WebSocket hint
# The Flask server also broadcasts via SocketIO. Use a SocketIO client to subscribe to 'gesture_update' events for real-time updates.
